# GitHub Profile Enhancer Environment Variables
# This is an example file showing what environment variables are available.
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in values as needed.

# GitHub API Configuration
# Note: This app uses the public GitHub REST API (v3)
# No build-time environment variables are required.
# Users can add their own GitHub token at runtime via the UI.

# Example: If you wanted to add a default token (NOT RECOMMENDED for public repos):
# REACT_APP_GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx

# Vercel Deployment Notes:
# - This is a Create React App project
# - No environment variables are required for deployment
# - Users will provide their own GitHub tokens via the UI modal
# - The app stores tokens only in browser memory (not persisted)

# API Endpoint Documentation:
# - Base URL: https://api.github.com
# - Users endpoint: /users/{username}
# - Repos endpoint: /users/{username}/repos
# - Rate limit: 60 requests/hour (unauthenticated), 5000/hour (authenticated)
